'''''andúnë''''' is the poetic word for "sunset", "west",<ref name=PE17>{{PE|17}}, p. 64</ref> or "evening" in [[Quenya]]. The more common word for "west" is '''''[[númen]]'''''. The capitalized form ''Andúnië'' is applied to the [[Aman|Uttermost West]] in the ''[[Namárië]]''.<ref>{{RGEO|5}}, p. 58</ref>

==Etymology==
''Andúnë'' derives from the [[Sundocarme|root]] NDŪ ("sink, go down").<ref name=PE17/>

==Cognates==
*[[Sindarin]], ''[[annûn]]''
*[[Adûnaic]], ''[[adûn]]''
